    "question": "If the probability of heads \\( p \\) is increased to \\( 0.8 \\) and tails \\( q \\) is \\( 0.2 \\), what is the probability of being in state \\( S_3 \\) after 3 tosses, given the initial conditions \\( S_1(1) = q \\), \\( S_2(1) = p \\), and \\( S_3(1) = 0 \\)?",
    "solution": "With \\( p = 0.8 \\) and \\( q = 0.2 \\), we will calculate \\( S_3(3) \\) using the same difference equations:\n\n1. \\( S_1(n) = q S_1(n-1) + q S_2(n-1) \\)\n2. \\( S_2(n) = p S_1(n-1) \\)\n3. \\( S_3(n) = p S_2(n-1) \\)\n\nStarting with the initial conditions:\n- \\( S_1(1) = q = 0.2 \\)\n- \\( S_2(1) = p = 0.8 \\)\n- \\( S_3(1) = 0 \\)\n\nNow we calculate \\( S_1(2) \\), \\( S_2(2) \\), and \\( S_3(2) \\):\n\n1. \\( S_1(2) = q S_1(1) + q S_2(1) = 0.2 \\cdot 0.2 + 0.2 \\cdot 0.8 = 0.04 + 0.16 = 0.2 \\)\n2. \\( S_2(2) = p S_1(1) = 0.8 \\cdot 0.2 = 0.16 \\)\n3. \\( S_3(2) = p S_2(1) = 0.8 \\cdot 0.8 = 0.64 \\)\n\nNext, we calculate \\( S_1(3) \\), \\( S_2(3) \\), and \\( S_3(3) \\):\n\n1. \\( S_1(3) = q S_1(2) + q S_2(2) = 0.2 \\cdot 0.2 + 0.2 \\cdot 0.16 = 0.04 + 0.032 = 0.072 \\)\n2. \\( S_2(3) = p S_1(2) = 0.8 \\cdot 0.2 = 0.16 \\)\n3. \\( S_3(3) = p S_2(2) = 0.8 \\cdot 0.16 = 0.128 \\)\n\nThus, the probability of being in state \\( S_3 \\) after 3 tosses is:\n\n\\[\n\\boxed{0.128}\n\\]",
